Firefighters rushed to Platt Drive Primary School in Isipingo Hills, where a fire broke out in the school kitchen area, a short while ago. An urgent plea for assistance was broadcasted via a local WhatsApp group and the relevant authorities and services were dispatched. According to local security company, PT Alarms, spokesperson, Dhevan Govindasamy said, “The PT Tactical Unit joined SAPS, firefighters and other emergency services, CPF members and security companies on the scene where firefighters swiftly worked to extinguish the flames. The kitchen area of the school was ablaze. The children were evacuated and removed to a place of safety.” He added, “There were no reported injuries but due to the dense smoke, a woman collapsed due to smoke inhalation and was treated on scene. The fire was extinguished and investigations are underway.”